Aï¸âƒ£ OWASP MOBILE TOP 10 â†’ TOOL & ACTION MATRIX

OWASP ID	Risk	What to Look For	Primary Tools	Defensive Outcome

M1	Improper Platform Usage	Exported components, insecure IPC, misused permissions	Drozer, MobSF, Androwarn	Lock components, enforce permission checks
M2	Insecure Data Storage	Secrets in APK, plaintext DB, logs	APKLeaks, Jadx, FlowDroid	Encrypt at rest, remove hardcoded secrets
M3	Insecure Communication	TLS bypass, weak cert pinning	apk-mitm, Frida, friTap	Enforce TLS, cert pinning
M4	Insecure Authentication	Weak auth flows, token reuse	MobSF (dyn), Frida	Strong auth, token rotation
M5	Insufficient Cryptography	Weak algorithms, bad RNG	Jadx, ClassyShark	Use modern crypto, proper key mgmt
M6	Insecure Authorization	Role bypass, logic flaws	Drozer, Frida	Server-side authZ
M7	Client Code Quality	Logic bugs, obfuscation gaps	Quark-Engine, Jadx	Harden logic, obfuscate properly
M8	Code Tampering	Repackaging, patching	FSquaDRA, Dexmod	Integrity checks
M9	Reverse Engineering	Easy RE, no protection	Apktool, Jadx, Radare2	Anti-RE, split logic
M10	Extraneous Functionality	Debug backdoors, test APIs	Jadx, Drozer	Remove dead/debug code



